INSTALLATION
============

Installing this war requires the following components:
- Glassfish 4
- JDK 7
- MySQL
- MySQL JConnect jdbc driver in glassfish ($GLASSFISH/glassfish/lib)
- JQuery (automatically connects to a CDN, so no worries there)
- Fancybox (Lightbox replacement for jquery, I'm using an old version,
  version jquery.fancybox-1.3.4.zip. To be on the safe side, I included it
  into git.)

Steps
-----

1. create a database
2. install Glassfish
3. Start Glassfish glassfish-4.0/bin/asadmin start-domain domain1
4. Put in an administration password, it asks for one.
5. Go to http://localhost:4848 en log in with user admin/password you just supplied
6. Install JDBC drivers for MySQL (or whatever databaseyou wish to use)
7. deploy the war to glassfish
8. deploy the fancybox stuff to ~GlassFish_Server/glassfish/domains/domain1/docroot (assuming defaults here)
9. Check the logs

Logging
-------

Add the following entries to glassfish3/glassfish/domains/domain1/config/logging.properties:

gallery.images.ImageOperations.level=FINEST
gallery.servlets.FileOperations.level=FINEST
gallery.servlets.ImageServlet.level=FINEST
gallery.beans.PhotographBean.level=FINEST
gallery.database.entities.Photograph.level=FINEST

Addendum
--------

Don't forget to properly specify the data source in glassfish.

The software is looking for a JDBC Resource named 
YourPersonalPhotographOrganiser.

